
First, we will create the components of our laboratory architecture (and then the testing
suite)

elements.py will contain:
    • A function create_fire() that just returns the string “Fire element created”.
    • A function create_water() that just returns the string “Water element created”.
    alchemy/elements.py will contain:
    • A function create_earth() that just returns the string “Earth element created”.
    • A function create_air() that just returns the string “Air element created”.

alchemy/__init__.py will contain:
    • Anything useful to partially import the alchemy module. See ft_alembic_4.py .
    In order to carefully test our laboratory architecture, create the following six scripts:
    • ft_alembic_0.py will use the import ... structure to access elements.py directly
    and then create fire.
    • ft_alembic_1.py will use the from ... import ... structure to access elements.py
    directly and then create water.
    • ft_alembic_2.py will use the import ... structure to access alchemy/elements.py
    directly and then create earth.
    
